## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="e7edd-116">En el ejemplo siguiente se crea una gramática que reconoce la frase "es de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo" seguido del nombre de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7edd-116">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e7edd-117">Después de crear el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objeto `winnerRule` y dándole el identificador de cadena `WorldCupWinner`, en el ejemplo se anexa la cadena "es de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo" para la regla.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7edd-117">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example appends the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e7edd-118">Uso de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objetos, en el ejemplo se compila una lista de países de Europa y una lista de países de América del Sur y agrega cada lista para su regla correspondiente, `ruleEurope` o `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7edd-118">Using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects, the example then builds a list of European countries and a list of South American countries, and adds each list to its respective rule, `ruleEurope` or `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="e7edd-119">El ejemplo crea, a continuación, las referencias de regla para `ruleEurope` y `ruleSAmerica` y los agrega a la `WorldCupWinner` regla.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7edd-119">The example then creates rule references for `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` and adds them to the `WorldCupWinner` rule.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e7edd-120">La gramática creada tiene la forma siguiente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7edd-120">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
